data.name: Androgynsexual_Description
data.value: Describes people attracted to those who possess both masculine and feminine traits. The attraction is based on the androgynous appearance of the person.

data.name: Androgynsexual_Name
data.value: Androgynsexual

data.name: Androsexual_Description
data.value: Refers to people who are attracted to men, males, or masculinity, including people who identify as men regardless of their biology or sex assigned at birth.

data.name: Androsexual_Name
data.value: Androsexual

data.name: Asexual_Description
data.value: A broad spectrum of people who experience little to no sexual attraction to others. Asexual people may still experience romantic attraction and form relationships, and may also identify with other specific terms on the asexual spectrum.

data.name: Asexual_Name
data.value: Asexual

data.name: Autosexual_Description
data.value: Describes a person who is sexually attracted to themselves. This concept is distinct from self-pleasure or masturbation and relates more to self-desire.

data.name: Autosexual_Name
data.value: Autosexual

data.name: Bisexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who experience sexual, romantic, or emotional attraction to more than one gender. This term is flexible and can encompass various forms of attraction to different genders.

data.name: Bisexual_Name
data.value: Bisexual

data.name: Demisexual_Description
data.value: Falls within the asexual spectrum, describing people who experience sexual attraction only after forming a deep emotional or romantic bond.

data.name: Demisexual_Name
data.value: Demisexual

data.name: Graysexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who exist in the “gray area” between asexuality and sexuality, experiencing occasional or conditional sexual attraction.

data.name: Graysexual_Name
data.value: Graysexual

data.name: Gynosexual_Description
data.value: Refers to people who are attracted to women, females, or femininity, including people who identify as women regardless of their biology or sex assigned at birth.

data.name: Gynosexual_Name
data.value: Gynosexual

data.name: Heterosexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who are sexually, romantically, or emotionally attracted to people of a different gender (e.g., men attracted to women and vice versa).

data.name: Heterosexual_Name
data.value: Heterosexual

data.name: Homosexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who experience sexual, romantic, or emotional attraction to people of the same gender. However, many prefer terms like "gay" or "lesbian" as "homosexual" can sometimes carry clinical or outdated connotations.

data.name: Homosexual_Name
data.value: Homosexual

data.name: Other_Description
data.value: This user identifies with a unique sexual orientation that does not conform to common categories.

data.name: Other_Name
data.value: Other

data.name: Pansexual_Description
data.value: Refers to people who can experience attraction to others regardless of their gender, embracing an openness to all genders and identities.

data.name: Pansexual_Name
data.value: Pansexual

data.name: Polysexual_Description
data.value: Refers to people who are attracted to multiple genders but not necessarily all genders. It differs from pansexuality in its focus on attraction to specific genders.

data.name: Polysexual_Name
data.value: Polysexual

data.name: Pomosexual_Description
data.value: A term used by people who reject sexuality labels or choose not to identify with any established sexual orientation. It is more of a rejection of categorization than a specific identity.

data.name: Pomosexual_Name
data.value: Pomosexual

data.name: Sapiosexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who are primarily attracted to intelligence or intellectual connection rather than physical or gender-based attraction.

data.name: Sapiosexual_Name
data.value: Sapiosexual

data.name: Skoliosexual_Description
data.value: Describes people who are attracted to individuals with non-cisgender identities, such as nonbinary, genderqueer, or transgender people.

data.name: Skoliosexual_Name
data.value: Skoliosexual
